remarks: Subclass inclusion with one element of the superclass missing is proper subclass inclusion.  Deduction form of ~ ssnelpss .  (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)
statement:
ssnelpssd.1 $e |- ( ph -> A C_ B ) $.
ssnelpssd.2 $e |- ( ph -> C e. B ) $.
ssnelpssd.3 $e |- ( ph -> -. C e. A ) $.
ssnelpssd $p |- ( ph -> A C. B ) $.
